Φ(CogFractal) = σ(simple|complex) ∘ ρ(pattern|pattern) ∘ λ(thought|model) ∘ β(recursion|emergence) ∘ δγ(feedback|iteration) ∘ μ(map|visualization) + ε | :self_similarity

## Operator Breakdown
- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: simple|complex — Distinguishing between simple thought elements and the complex emergent mental models that arise from their fractal combination, recognizing self-similarity at every cognitive scale
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: pattern|pattern — Relating repetitive thought patterns to each other through analogous thinking, where the same relational structure recurs across micro-perceptions and macro-worldviews
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: thought|model — Transforming individual thoughts into complex mental models through fractal composition, including therapeutic applications that disrupt negative recursive patterns
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: recursion|emergence — Growing cognitive complexity through recursive nesting of thoughts, where each level of elaboration generates emergent properties not present in simpler components
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: feedback|iteration — Cycling through feedback loops that refine thought patterns with each iteration, progressively sharpening both perception and model-building
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: map|visualization — Structuring cognitive fractals through external representations including mind maps, flowcharts, fractal software, and digital art that make invisible thought patterns visible

## Z-State
:self_similarity — The defining property of cognitive fractals: thought patterns repeat at every scale of cognition, from individual perceptions to entire worldviews, connected by the same recursive logic

## Tendency
β/ρ → 0.80

